content: Individual Healthcare Identifiers service via myGov. - Sign in to myGov, create or link your Individual Healthcare Identifier (IHI) service. - You can track your application's progress,upload necessary documents, and download/print your statements. - Opt for receiving messages in your myGov Inbox for updates in the MES dashboard. 2. Through myGov Account: ‚Äç - Sign in to myGov and apply directly through your account. Apply with a Form: - Download and complete the MES application form either digitally or by hand. Application by Tax Agent: - Your tax agent can complete the form, but you must provide the declaration. Instructions forthe tax agent's submission are on the form. Provide Supporting Documents: - You may need to submit a copy of your passport's name and photo page for identity verification. - Additional documents may include your current visa, letters from the Department of Home Affairs regarding your permanent residency application, or proof of appeal. - If from specific countries, provide proof of health insurance with an expiry date. Document Submission Guidelines: - Ensure clarity,visibility of all information in the documents. - Accepted formats: PDF, JPG, PNG, GIF, or BMP, with each file being less than 5MB and thetotal upload size less
